# Modus Navbar + Side Navigation - Short

Critical integration patterns for Modus Navbar with Side Navigation in SolidJS.

## Key Rules

- **Use ModusNavbar/ModusSideNavigation wrapper components** - Never use raw web components directly
- **Menu item icons use the `start-icon` slot** - Render `<i class="modus-icons" slot="start-icon">name</i>` as child, NOT `start-icon` prop
- **Sync hamburger with side nav** - Use `mainMenuOpen`/`onMainMenuOpenChange` + `expanded`/`onExpandedChange`
- **Independent state per section** - Separate components with own `createSignal` to avoid interference
- **Contain in fixed-height `overflow-hidden`** - Prevents page layout shifts when side nav expands
- **Trimble logo assets** - Need `defineCustomElements(window, { resourcesUrl: origin + "/" })` and static copy to both `modus-wc/assets` and `assets`

## ModusNavbar Custom Content Slots

Use `centerContent` and `endContent` slots for custom navbar content:

```tsx
<ModusNavbar
  userCard={{ name: "Jane Smith", email: "jane@trimble.com" }}
  visibility={{ mainMenu: false, notifications: true, apps: true, help: true, user: true }}
  centerContent={<div class="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Project Name</div>}
  endContent={<ModusButton color="primary" size="sm" variant="outlined">Invite</ModusButton>}
/>
```

## ModusSideNavigation Limitations

- **Flat items only** - `ModusSideNavigation` accepts a flat `MenuItem[]` array. It does NOT support nested/hierarchical items, expandable sub-sections, or grouped navigation
- **If you need nested navigation** (expandable sections like "Records > RFIs, Submittals..." or "Financials > Budget, Contracts..."), build a custom sidebar using div elements with `createSignal<boolean>` for expand/collapse state per section
- **Active state** - Use `@solidjs/router`'s `useLocation()` to detect active path and apply active styling (e.g., `bg-primary-20 text-primary border-l-2 border-primary`)

